= [[George Cole Field]]\n|champion = [[1979 NCAA Division I Baseball Tournament#East Regional|East Regional Champions]]\n|bowl=[[1979 College World Series|College World Series]], Runner-Up\n}}\n{{1979 Southwest Conference baseball standings}}\nThe '''1979 Arkansas Razorbacks baseball team''' represented the [[University of Arkansas]] in the [[1979 NCAA Division I baseball season]]. The Razorbacks played their home games at [[George Cole Field]], and was led by tenth year head coach [[Norm DeBriyn]]. They finished as the national runner-up after falling to [[1979 Cal State Fullerton Titans baseball team|Cal State Fullerton]] in the 1979 College World Series Final.\n\n==Roster==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"text-align: left; font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"9\" style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Arkansas Razorbacks}}; text-align:center;\"| 1979 Arkansas Razorbacks roster\n|-\n|width=\"03\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n'''[[Pitcher]]s'''\n* Rich Erwin\n* Steve Krueger\n* Scott Tabor\n\n|width=\"15\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n'''[[Catcher]]s'''\n* [[Ronn Reynolds]]\n\n'''[[Infielder]]s'''\n* [[Johnny Ray (baseball)|Johnny Ray]]\n\n|width=\"15\"|&nbsp;\n| valign=\"top\" |\n\n|width=\"15\"|&nbsp;\n| valign=\"top\" |\n'''Coaching staff'''\n* [[Norm DeBriyn]] \u2013  Head Coach\n|}\n\n==Schedule==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Legend\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#ddffdd\"|&nbsp;||Arkansas win\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"#ffdddd\"|&nbsp;||Arkansas loss\n|}\n\n{| class=\"toccolours\" width=95% style=\"clear:both; margin:1.5em auto; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Arkansas Razorbacks|color=white}}\" | 1979 Arkansas Razorbacks Baseball Game Log\n|-\n! colspan=2 style=\"{{CollegeSecondaryStyle|Arkansas Razorbacks}}\" | Regular Season\n|- valign=\"top\" \n|<div class=\"NavFrame\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Arkansas Razorbacks}};\">February (4\u20130)</div>\n<div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"text-align:left;