{"title_page": "Vystavka, Votlazhemsky Selsoviet, Kotlassky District, Arkhangelsk Oblast", "text_new": "{{Other places3|Vystavka}}\n{{short description|Rural locality in Arkhangelsk Oblast, Russia}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Vystavka\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Arkhangelsk Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Arkhangelsk Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Kotlassky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|61|05|34|N|46|36|52|E|display=inline}}\n}}\n'''Vystavka''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[village#Russia|village]]) in Votlazhemsky Selsoviet of [[Kotlassky District]] of [[Arkhangelsk Oblast]], [[Russia]]. The population was 171 as of 2010.<ref>[http://arhangelskstat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/arhangelskstat/resources/2edc58004f857ef7ae20af9b972d8349/%D1%87%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%8C.doc \u0412\u0441\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f 2010 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430. \u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u043e \u043c\u0443\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043f\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f\u043c \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0410\u0440\u0445\u0430\u043d\u0433\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n\nIt is the largest rural locality in the [[selsoviet]], with the population of 202 as of January 2005.<ref>[http://www.arhpress.ru/dvinskaya/2005/2/18/6.shtml \"\u0421\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0441\u043b\u0435\u043f\u043e\u043a \u0431\u0435\u0434\u044b\"], \u0414\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430, 18 \u0444\u0435\u0432\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044f 2005 (28) (retrieved August 28, 2013) {{in lang|ru}}</ref> \n\nWithin the [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|framework of municipal divisions]], the village has since 2006 been a part of Cheryomushskoye Rural Settlement.<ref>[http://xn--e1aaatjnkkr9aq.xn--p1ai/regulatory/files/charter_of_the_municipality.php?ELEMENT_ID=262 Statute of Cheryomushskoye Municipality]</ref>\n\n{{Interlanguage link multi|Votlazhma Trinity Church|ru|3=\u0412\u043e\u0442\u043b\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c}} is located in Vystavka. The baroque church was built in 1753 and was closed for service in 1932. It is now deserted and neglected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sobory.ru/article/?object=06443|script-title=ru:\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430 (\u0412\u043e\u0442\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u0442). \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u044b \u0416\u0438\u0432\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439|publisher=sobory,ru|language=Russian|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref> The church is designated as a cultural heritage monument of local significance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kulturnoe-nasledie.ru/monuments.php?id=2900405000|script-title=ru:\u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0412\u043e\u0442\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f|publisher=Ministry of Culture of Russian Federation|language=Russian|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Rural localities in Kotlassky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Arkhangelsk Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Kotlassky District]]\n\n{{ArkhangelskOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Other places3|Vystavka}}\n{{short description|Rural locality in Arkhangelsk Oblast, Russia}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Vystavka\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Arkhangelsk Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Arkhangelsk Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Kotlassky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|61|05|34|N|46|36|52|E|display=inline}}\n}}\n'''Vystavka''' ({{lang-ru|\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[village#Russia|village]]) in Votlazhemsky Selsoviet of [[Kotlassky District]] of [[Arkhangelsk Oblast]], [[Russia]]. The population was 171 as of 2010.<ref>[http://arhangelskstat.gks.ru/wps/wcm/connect/rosstat_ts/arhangelskstat/resources/2edc58004f857ef7ae20af9b972d8349/%D1%87%D0%B8%D1%81%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%8C.doc \u0412\u0441\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f 2010 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430. \u0427\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u043e \u043c\u0443\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043f\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0437\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f\u043c \u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u044b\u043c \u043f\u0443\u043d\u043a\u0442\u0430\u043c \u0410\u0440\u0445\u0430\u043d\u0433\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n\nIt is the largest rural locality in the [[selsoviet]], with the population of 202 as of January 2005.<ref>[http://www.arhpress.ru/dvinskaya/2005/2/18/6.shtml \"\u0421\u0435\u043b\u044c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0441\u043b\u0435\u043f\u043e\u043a \u0431\u0435\u0434\u044b\"], \u0414\u0432\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0434\u0430, 18 \u0444\u0435\u0432\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044f 2005 (28) (retrieved August 28, 2013) {{in lang|ru}}</ref> \n\nWithin the [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|framework of municipal divisions]], the village has since 2006 been a part of Cheryomushskoye Rural Settlement.<ref>[http://xn--e1aaatjnkkr9aq.xn--p1ai/regulatory/files/charter_of_the_municipality.php?ELEMENT_ID=262 Statute of Cheryomushskoye Municipality]</ref>\n\n{{Interlanguage link multi|Votlazhma Trinity Church|ru|3=\u0412\u043e\u0442\u043b\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043c\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c}} is located in Vystavka. The baroque church was built in 1753 and was closed for service in 1932. It is now deserted and neglected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sobory.ru/article/?object=06443|script-title=ru:\u0412\u044b\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0430 (\u0412\u043e\u0442\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0441\u0442). \u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u044b \u0416\u0438\u0432\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439|publisher=sobory,ru|language=Russian|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref> The church is designated as a cultural heritage monument of local significance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kulturnoe-nasledie.ru/monuments.php?id=2900405000|script-title=ru:\u0426\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c \u0422\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0446\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0412\u043e\u0442\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f|publisher=Ministry of Culture of Russian Federation|language=Russian|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Rural localities in Kotlassky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Arkhangelsk Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Kotlassky District]]\n\n\n{{ArkhangelskOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vystavka,_Votlazhemsky_Selsoviet,_Kotlassky_District,_Arkhangelsk_Oblast"}
{"title_page": "Penny Lancaster", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name= Penny, Lady Stewart\n| image=Pennylancaster.jpg\n| caption=Penny Lancaster in 2008\n| birth_name= Penny Lancaster\n| birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1971|3|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place= [[Chelmsford]], [[Essex]], England\n| height= {{convert|1.85|m|ftin|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite news|title=Eight ways short people disguise their height|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/8243763.stm|work=[[BBC News Online]]|date=8 September 2009}}</ref>\n| haircolour= Blonde\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Sir Rod Stewart]]|2007}}\n| children = 2\n}}\n'''Penny, Lady Stewart''' (''n\u00e9e'' '''Lancaster'''; born 15 March 1971), is an English [[Model (person)|model]], [[photographer]] and [[TV personality]]. She is married to rock singer [[Sir Rod Stewart]]. In 2014, she joined the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] lunchtime show ''[[Loose Women]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nLancaster was brought up by parents Graham and Sally who were both regular gym-goers and encouraged a love of fitness. She also has a brother named Oliver. At the age of six, Lancaster took up dance, learning [[tap dance|tap]], [[ballet]] and [[modern dance|modern]] but decided to quit at the age of 16 due to her height and decided [[aerobics]] would better suit her frame. Six years later Lancaster became a certified [[personal trainer|fitness trainer]]. It was during this time that she was spotted by a model scout who suggested she should consider a career in [[Model (person)|modelling]]. Lancaster  suffers from chronic sweat problem called [[hyperhidrosis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/770693/Penny-Lancaster-SWEATING-Hyperhidrosis-Loose-Women|title=Penny Lancaster admits SWEATING excessively due to secret battle with Hyperhidrosis}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Early career===\nThroughout the 1990s, Lancaster was in a long-term relationship with city trader Mickey Sloan. They lived in [[Bermuda]] from 1996 to 1998 but separated in 1999.\n\nAround this time, Lancaster decided to learn about the other side of modelling and began taking [[photography]] classes.<ref>{{cite news | title='Penny Lancaster' | publisher=[[AskMen.com]] | url=http://uk.askmen.com/women/models_250/293c_penny_lancaster.html | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071112103500/http://uk.askmen.com/women/models_250/293c_penny_lancaster.html | archivedate=12 November 2007 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Ultimo===\nIn 2002, Lancaster signed up to be the face of designer lingerie brand [[Ultimo (lingerie)|Ultimo]] for a reported \u00a3200,000. Although she was a success at promoting the brand - raising its profile, especially in the United Kingdom - two years later, Lancaster's contract was not renewed.<ref>{{Cite news| title='Storm in a D-cup' |date=18 January 2004| accessdate=18 January 2004 | publisher=[[Scotsman.com]] | url=http://www.business.scotsman.com/topics.cfm?tid=509&id=62742004}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/ROD%27S+MISSING+BHOYS+FOR+ME%3B+The+face+and+body+of+Ultimo,+Penny...-a0106964724 |title=Rod's Missing Bhoys for Me; The face and body of Ultimo, Penny Lancaster, reveals how her rocker lover will be watching her instead of his beloved Celtic this weekend |publisher=[[The Free Library]] |work=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]] |date=2003-08-28 |accessdate=2016-03-07}}</ref> She was replaced in the role by [[Rod Stewart]]'s ex-wife [[Rachel Hunter]]. The decision, dubbed \"Bra Wars\" by the British press, was seen as a publicity stunt <ref>{{cite web|first1=Richard |last1=Simpson |first2=Alexa |last2=Baracaia |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/pennys-1m-revenge-7225559.html |title=Penny's \u00a31m revenge |work=[[London Evening Standard]] |date=2004-05-18 |accessdate=2016-03-07}}</ref>  which infuriated Stewart who described the money-grabber as \"manipulative\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Rod%27s+revenge%3B+STAR+SLAMS+BRA+OUEEN+-+Ultimo+boss+is+a+manipulative...-a0114675089 |title=Rod's revenge; Star Slams Bra Queen |publisher=[[The Free Library]] |work=[[Sunday Mail (Scotland)|Sunday Mail]] |date=2004-03-28 |accessdate=2016-03-07}}</ref> However, two of Stewart's daughters - [[Kimberly Stewart|Kimberly]] and [[Ruby Stewart|Ruby]] - have since modelled for Ultimo.\n\n===''Strictly Come Dancing''===\n\nLancaster was announced as one of the fourteen celebrities taking part in the [[Strictly Come Dancing (series 5)|fifth series]] of ''[[Strictly Come Dancing]]'' in 2007. In week 4, she was revealed as one of the bottom two participants. She and her partner ([[Ian Waite]]) were in the week six dance-off with [[Matt Di Angelo]] and were voted off.\n\n'''Performances'''\n{|class=\"wikitable\" align=\"left\"\n|rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" align=\"Center\"|'''Week #'''\n|rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" align=\"Center\"|'''Dance'''\n|colspan=\"4\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" align=\"Center\"|'''Judges' score'''\n|rowspan=\"2\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" align=\"Center\"|'''Result'''\n|-\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" width=\"10%\" align=\"center\"|Revel Horwood\n|bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" width=\"10%\" align=\"center\"|Phillips\n|bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" width=\"10%\" align=\"center\"|Goodman\n|bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\" width=\"10%\" align=\"center\"|Tonioli\n|-\n|-\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|1\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|[[Swing (dance)|Swing]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\"|\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\"|\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\"|\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"CCCCCC\"|\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|Group Performance - Not Judged\n|-\n|-\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|2\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|[[Quickstep]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|8\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|8\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|8\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|9\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|Safe\n|-\n|-\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|3\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|[[Jive (dance)|Jive]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|5\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|6\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|7\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|7\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|Safe\n|-\n|-\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|4\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|[[Samba]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|8\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|7\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|9\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|8\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|Bottom Two\n|-\n|-\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|5\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|[[Foxtrot]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|9\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|8\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|9\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|9\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|Safe\n|-\n|-\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|6\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|[[Salsa (dance)|Salsa]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|6\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|6\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|7\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|6\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"FAF6F6\"|''Eliminated''\n|}{{Clear}}\n\n===''Loose Women''===\n{{main|Loose Women}}\nOn 15 September 2014, Lancaster was billed as an occasional panelist on the lunchtime chat show ''[[Loose Women]]''. Through series 19 of the show, she made four subsequent appearances, on 1 December 2014, 9 March 2015, 15 June 2015, 6 July 2015. Since series 20 began on 1 September 2015, Lancaster now appears more regularly and has so far appeared three times in September 2015, once in October and November 2015, twice in December 2015, twice in January 2016, twice in March 2016, twice in April 2016, twice in May 2016 and once in June 2016. As of series 21 which began on 5 September 2016, Lancaster now appears weekly.\n\n===Other television work===\n\nIn January 2018, Penny participated in ''[[And They're Off!]]'' in aid of [[Sport Relief]].\n\nIn February 2019 she appeared in ''Famous and Fighting Crime'' alongside fellow celebrities [[Jamie Laing]], [[Katie Piper]], [[Sandi Bogle]] and [[Marcus Brigstocke]] on [[Channel 4]].\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 1999, Lancaster met singer [[Rod Stewart]], when he agreed to let her take photos of him whilst on tour.<ref>{{cite magazine|title='Rod's girl Penny all set for 'perfect' wedding'|date=6 June 2007|accessdate=6 June 2007|magazine=[[Hello! (magazine)|Hello!]]|url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2007/06/06/penny-rod-wedding/}}</ref> A romance soon developed and they began a lengthy courtship. Seven years on, Rod went down on one knee and asked for her hand in marriage at the top of the Eiffel Tower, though the wedding plans were halted when Penny discovered she was expecting the couple's first child. Lancaster gave birth to her first child, Alastair Wallace Stewart on 27 November 2005.<ref>{{cite magazine|title='Rod Stewart's Fianc\u00e9e Gives Birth'|date=28 November 2005|accessdate=28 November 2005|magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]]|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1135159,00.html}}</ref> Lancaster and Stewart married on 16 June 2007 at La Cervara near [[Portofino]], [[Italy]]. The couple exchanged vows in the presence of family and friends.<ref>{{cite magazine|title='Rod Stewart Marries Penny Lancaster in Italy'|date=17 June 2007|accessdate=17 July 2007|magazine=People|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20042844,00.html}}</ref> On 17 February 2011, it was announced that Lancaster had given birth to their second child (Stewart's eighth child), Aiden Patrick Stewart.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-12500132|publisher=BBC News|title=Rod Stewart and Penny Lancaster celebrate birth of boy|date=17 February 2011}}</ref> \n\nLancaster is an ambassador for Penny for London.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/567339/Penny-Lancaster-charity-help-young-people-in-poverty|title=Penny Lancaster backs charity to help young people in poverty|author=John Reynolds|newspaper=Daily Express}}</ref> She is also a vice-president of the [[RNIB]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aop.org.uk/ot/industry/eyewear-and-lenses/2016/10/20/penny-lancaster-me-and-my-glasses|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109021617/https://www.aop.org.uk/ot/industry/eyewear-and-lenses/2016/10/20/penny-lancaster-me-and-my-glasses|url-status=dead|archive-date=2016-11-09|title=Me and my glasses: Photographer Penny Lancaster speaks about her vision and why she is supporting the State of the Nation Report: Eye health 2016|author=Emily McCormick|work=Optometry Today}}</ref>\n\nAt the age of 46, Lancaster was diagnosed with [[dyslexia]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2018012245630/penny-lancaster-diagnosed-dyslexia/|title=Penny Lancaster diagnosed with learning difficulty|magazine=Hello!|date=22 January 2018|author=Gemma Strong}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Clear}}\n{{Reflist|2}}\n<!-- Dead note \"mariage\": [http://tf1.lci.fr/infos/people/0,,3471594,00-rod-stewart-marie-pour-fois-.html Actualit\u00e9 TF1 2007, 16 June 2007 ] -->\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=1519592|name=Penny Lancaster}}\n*{{Instagram|penny.lancaster}}\n{{Rod Stewart}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lancaster, Penny}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English female models]]\n[[Category:People from Chelmsford]]\n[[Category:Family of Rod Stewart]]\n[[Category:English photographers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2012}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name= Penny, Lady Stewart\n| image=Pennylancaster.jpg\n| caption=Penny Lancaster in 2008\n| birth_name= Penny Lancaster\n| birth_date= {{Birth date and age|1971|3|15|df=y}}\n| birth_place= [[Chelmsford]], [[Essex]], England\n| height= {{convert|1.85|m|ftin|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite news|title=Eight ways short people disguise their height|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/magazine/8243763.stm|work=[[BBC News Online]]|date=8 September 2009}}</ref>\n| haircolour= Blonde\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Sir Rod Stewart]]|2007}}\n| children = 2\n}}\n'''Penny, Lady Stewart''' (''n\u00e9e'' '''Lancaster'''; born 15 March 1971), is an English [[Model (person)|model]], [[photographer]] and [[TV personality]]. She is married to rock singer [[Sir Rod Stewart]]. In 2014, she joined the [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] lunchtime show ''[[Loose Women]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nLancaster was brought up by parents Graham and Sally who were both regular gym-goers and encouraged a love of fitness. She also has a brother named Oliver. At the age of six, Lancaster took up dance, learning [[tap dance|tap]], [[ballet]] and [[modern dance|modern]] but decided to quit at the age of 16 due to her height and decided [[aerobics]] would better suit her frame. Six years later Lancaster became a certified [[personal trainer|fitness trainer]]. It was during this time that she was spotted by a model scout who suggested she should consider a career in [[Model (person)|modelling]]. Lancaster  suffers from chronic sweat problem called [[hyperhidrosis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.express.co.uk/showbiz/tv-radio/770693/Penny-Lancaster-SWEATING-Hyperhidrosis-Loose-Women|title=Penny Lancaster admits SWEATING excessively due to secret battle with Hyperhidrosis}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Early career===\nThroughout the 1990s, Lancaster was in a long-term relationship with city trader Mickey Sloan. They lived in [[Bermuda]] from 1996 to 1998 but separated in 1999.\n\nAround this time, Lancaster decided to learn about the other side of modelling and began taking [[photography]] classes.<ref>{{cite news | title='Penny Lancaster' | publisher=[[AskMen.com]] | url=http://uk.askmen.com/women/models_250/293c_penny_lancaster.html | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071112103500/http://u